 FRDDB2   06:34:04.217607 * The desired setting for Stayresident is YES in Production
 FRDDB2   06:34:04.217623 * The IBM Debug Tool requires Stayresident NO, ergo the TEST and INTE
 FRDDB2   06:34:04.217642 *     setting of NO
 FRDDB2   06:34:04.217678 * There are some stored procedures (espically on C) that are not
 FRDDB2   06:34:04.217698 * coded properly and require Stayresident=NO -- without the NO setting
 FRDDB2   06:34:04.217717 * these stored procedures abend 0C4/0C1/0C7 intermittently because they
 FRDDB2   06:34:04.217737 * are not properly initializing their storage
 FRDDB2   06:34:04.217753 *
 FRDDB2   06:34:04.217772 DB2TESTStayresident=NO
 FRDDB2   06:34:04.217789 DB2INTEStayresident=NO
 FRDDB2   06:34:04.217808 DB2QUALStayresident=YES
 FRDDB2   06:34:04.217825 DB2EDUCStayresident=YES
 FRDDB2   06:34:04.217844 DB2PRODStayresident=YES

 FRDDB2   06:34:04.217940 * *** NOTE ***   Ford Credit and Brazil and Europe have
 FRDDB2   06:34:04.217964 *                additional RACF groups so will need set in
 FRDDB2   06:34:04.217990 *                DEFAULTf

    000251               *  BATCH MESSAGE PROGRAM RESTART AREA                           * 00020900
    000252               *                                                               * 00021000
    000253               * THIS COPY MEMBER DEFINES THE RESTART AREA. THIS AREA IS USED  * 00021100
    000254               * IN "XRST" AND "CHKP" CALLS TO SAVE THE VALUES OF WORKING-     * 00021200
    000255               * STORAGE VARIABLES. THE AREA "WS-APPL-SPECIFIC-XRST-DATA" IS   * 00021300
    000256               * TO BE USED TO STORE APPLICATION-SPECIFIC DATA. THIS DATA MUST * 00021400
    000257               * BE SAVED WHEN A CHECKPOINT IS TAKEN, AND RESTORED WHEN AN     * 00021500
    000258               * IMS OR INTERNAL RESTART IS DONE.  NOTE THAT THERE IS A        * 00021600
    000259               * MAXIMUM LENGTH TO THIS AREA.                                  * 00021700
    000260               *                                                               * 00021800
    000261               * YOU MAY SAVE OTHER AREAS IN YOUR PROGRAM BY ADDING THEM TO    * 00021900
    000262               * THE XRST CALL IN PARA. 1010A AND THE CHKP CALL IN PARA.       * 00022000
    000263               * 6120A.  BUT SAVE (AND RESTORE) FROM (AND TO) COPIES OF        * 00022100
    000264               * THE DESIRED DATA, NOT THE "ORIGINALS."   WHEN A RESTART       * 00022200
    000265               * IS DONE, YOU OVERLAY THE "ORIGINALS" WITH THE "COPIES".       * 00022300
    000266               * ON IMS RESTARTS, IMS RESTORES THE SAVED DATA FOR YOU.  IF     * 00022400
    000267               * THE RESTART IS AN INTERNAL ONE (I.E., RECOVERY FROM A DEAD-   * 00022500
    000268               * LOCK), THE COPIES ARE THE ONLY SOURCES OF SAVED DATA.         * 00022600
    000269               *                                                               * 00022700

    006542C        000200***************************************************************** 0000000
    006543C        000300*                                                               * 0000000
    006544C        000400*  THIS PARAGRAPH CONTROLS THE PROCESSING OF A REQUEST.         * 0000000
    006545C        000500*  FIRST, PARAGRAPH 3100A IS PERFORMED TO ALLOW THE             * 0000000
    006546C        000600*  APPLICATION TO PREPARE FOR THE REQUEST.  NEXT, PARAGRAPH     * 0000000
    006547C        000700*  3500A IS PERFORMED UNTIL THE REQUEST IS COMPLETE (USUALLY    * 0000000
    006548C        000800*  BECAUSE THERE ARE NO MORE DRIVING RECORDS).  NEXT, PARA-     * 0000000
    006549C        000900*  GRAPH 3400A IS PERFORMED SO THE APPLICATION PROGRAM MAY      * 0000000
    006550C        001000*  PERFORM POST-REQUEST PROCESSING.                             * 0000000
    006551C        001100*                                                               * 0000000

    006556C        001600*    REQUEST-COMPLETE SWITCH BECAUSE THE PROGRAM MAY BE         * 0000000
    006557C        001700*    RECOVERING FROM A RESTART.  IF THE PROGRAM WAS IN THE      * 0000000
    006558C        001800*    MIDDLE OF A REQUEST WHEN THE CHECKPOINT WAS TAKEN, WE      * 0000000
    006559C        001900*    DON'T WANT TO PERFORM THE BEGIN-PROCESS NOW.               * 0000000

    006735C*       000100 3500H-PROCESS.                                                   0000000
    006736C        000200***************************************************************** 0000000
    006737C        000300*                                                               * 0000000
    006738C        000400*  THIS PARAGRAPH IS THE MAIN LINE DRIVER.  IF PRIMING-READ-    * 0000000
    006739C        000500*  REQUESTED, A "DRIVING RECORD" HAS ALREADY BEEN FETCHED BY    * 0000000
    006740C        000600*  PARAGRAPH 5000A. THIS RECORD IS THEN PROCESSED, THE          * 0000000
    006741C        000700*  CHECKPOINT COUNTER IS INCREMENTED, AND ANOTHER DRIVING       * 0000000
    006742C        000800*  RECORD IS READ.  IF THE CHECKPOINT COUNTER HAS REACHED       * 0000000
    006743C        000900*  ITS LIMIT, A CHECKPOINT IS TAKEN.                            * 0000000
    006744C        001000*  IF PRIMING-READ-REQUESTED IS FALSE, THE DRIVING RECORD       * 0000000
    006745C        001100*  IS FETCHED AT THE BEGINNING OF THE PARAGRAPH INSTEAD OF      * 0000000
    006746C        001200*  THE END, SO THE CHECKPOINT REFLECTS THE STATE OF THE         * 0000000
    006747C        001300*  PROGRAM AFTER THE RECORD HAS BEEN PROCESSED, RATHER THAN     * 0000000
    006748C        001400*  BEFORE.                                                      * 0000000
    006749C        001500*                                                               * 0000000
    006750C        001600***************************************************************** 0000000
    006751C        001700*                                                                 0000000
    006752C        001800     IF PRIMING-READ-REQUESTED                                    0000000  667
    006753C     1  001900         NEXT SENTENCE                                            0000000
    006754C        002000     ELSE                                                         0000000
    006755C     1  002100         PERFORM  5000A-GET-NEXT-DRIVING-RECORD                   0000000  8178
    006756C     1  002200            THRU  5000A-EXIT                                      0000000  8204
    006757C     1  002210         IF INTERNAL-RESTART                                      0000000  481
    006758C     2  002220             GO TO 3500H-EXIT.                                    0000000  6790
    006759C        002300                                                                  0000000
    006760C        002400     IF  DRIVING-RECORD-OBTAINED                                  0000000  374

    006762C     1  002900            THRU  3600A-EXIT                                      0000000  6936
    006763C     1  002910         IF INTERNAL-RESTART                                      0000000  481
    006764C     2  002920             GO TO 3500H-EXIT                                     0000000  6790
    006765C     1  002930         END-IF                                                   0000000

    006800               *                                                               * 00142500
    006801               *  THIS PARAGRAPH SHOULD DRIVE THE PROCESSING OF A UNIT OF      * 00142600
    006802               *  WORK. SPECIAL CONSIDERATION:                                 * 00142700
    006803               *                                                               * 00142800
    006804               *       THE CODE MUST ALLOW FOR DEADLOCK SITUATIONS. THIS IS    * 00142900
    006805               *       WHEN THE PROGRAM HAS "LOCKED" A RESOURCE THAT ANOTHER   * 00143000
    006806               *       PROGRAM NEEDS, AND VICE VERSA. THIS WILL BE SIGNALED    * 00143100
    006807               *       BY THE FOLLOWING:                                       * 00143200
    006808               *                                                               * 00143300
    006809               *           DB2:        SQLCODE = -911                          * 00143400
    006810               *                                                               * 00143500
    006811               *       WHEN THIS CONDITION OCCURS, THE PROGRAMMER              * 00143600
    006812               *       IS RESPONSIBLE FOR PERFORMIMG 6500A-DETECT-             * 00143700
    006813               *       INTERNAL-RESTART.                                       * 00143800
    006814               *                                                               * 00143900
    006815               *       IMS WILL NOT RETURN A STATUS OF FD (DEADLOCK). INSTEAD  * 00144000
    006816               *       IT WILL WAIT TO GET CONTROL OF THE RESOURCES IT NEEDS.  * 00144100
    006817               *       IF IT SHOULD TIME OUT, A SYSTEM ABEND IS PERFORMED AND  * 00144200
    006818               *       CONTROL IS NOT PASSED BACK TO YOUR PROGRAM.             * 00144300
    006819               *                                                               * 00144400

    009225                6500A-DETECT-INTERNAL-RESTART.                                   00366300
    009226               ***************************************************************** 00366400
    009227               *                                                               * 00366500
    009228               *  THIS PARAGRAPH CHECKS THE "SQLCODE" RETURNED FROM A DB2      * 00366600
    009229               *  CALL. IF THE CODE INDICATES THAT THE PROGRAM HAS BEEN RE-    * 00366700
    009230               *  STARTED AFTER A DEADLOCK SITUATION ("DEADLY EMBRACE"), THEN  * 00366800
    009231               *  THIS PARAGRAPH SETS THE APPROPRIATE SWITCH. THE PROGRAM      * 00366900
    009232               *  THEN ATTEMPTS TO CONTINUE PROCESSING. SHOULD THIS SITUATION  * 00367000
    009233               *  OCCUR AGAIN, THIS PARAGRAPH COUNTS THE NUMBER OF TIMES IT    * 00367100
    009234               *  HAS BEEN INVOKED ("WS-INTERNAL-RESTART-COUNTER").  IF IT BE  * 00367200
    009235               *  INVOKED TOO MANY TIMES (PERS2PS INDICATING A RECURRENT LOOP) * 00367300
    009236               *  IT SETS "SW-INTERNAL-RESTART-LIMIT-REACHED".  THE PROGRAM    * 00367400
    009237               *  WILL THEN ABNORMALLY TERMINATE.                              * 00367500
    009238               *                                                               * 00367600
    009239               *  IF THIS PARAGRAPH IS BEING PERFORMED AS INDICATED IN PARA    * 00367700
    009240               *  3600A-PROCESS-BATCH-UOW, UNCOMMENT THE FOLLOWING CODE.       * 00367800
    009241               *                                                               * 00367900
    009242               ***************************************************************** 00368000
    009243                                                                                 00368100
    009244                    IF  SQLCODE  EQUAL  WS-SQLCODE-DEADLOCK                      00368200 4956 579
    009245      1                 SET INTERNAL-RESTART TO TRUE                             00368300 481
    009246      1                 ADD +1  TO  WS-INTERNAL-RESTART-COUNTER                  00368400 454
    009247      1                 IF  WS-INTERNAL-RESTART-COUNTER  GREATER THAN            00368500 454
    009248      1                             WS-INTERNAL-RESTART-MAX                      00368600 697
    009249      2                     SET INTERNAL-RESTART-LIMIT-REACHED TO TRUE.          00368700 486
    009250                                                                                 00368800
    009251                6500A-EXIT.                                                      00368900
    009252                    EXIT.                                                        00369000

    009255C*       000010 7000H-OBTAIN-BATCH-REQUESTS.                                     0000000
    009256C        000100***************************************************************** 0000000
    009257C        000200*                                                               * 0000000
    009258C        000300* THIS PARAGRAPH IS USED TO FETCH REQUESTS FROM THE BATCH       * 0000000
    009259C        000400* REQUEST TABLE. SINCE REQUESTS ARE STORED IN A TABLE, AND      * 0000000
    009260C        000500* THE "HS2PBRTI" ROUTINE RETRIEVES THEM ONE AT A TIME, THE      * 0000000
    009261C        000600* ROUTINE MUST BE INVOKED MANY TIMES TO RETRIEVE A SET OF       * 0000000
    009262C        000700* REQUESTS.                                                     * 0000000
    009263C        000800*                                                               * 0000000
    009264C        000900* REQUESTS ARE GROUPED BY "TYPE". TYPES ARE DEFINED IN          * 0000000
    009265C        001000* WORKING-STORAGE. UP TO  8  REQUESTS OF A PARTICULAR TYPE      * 0000000
    009266C        001100* MAY BE PROCESSED SIMULTANEOUSLY (APPLICATION-DEPENDENT).      * 0000000
    009267C        001200* THIS ALLOWS THE APPLICATION TO EFFICIENTLY TRAVERSE A DATA    * 0000000
    009268C        001300* BASE OR TABLE.                                                * 0000000
    009269C        001400*                                                               * 0000000
    009270C        001500* SEVERAL (UP TO  3) DIFFERENT TYPES OF REQUESTS MAY BE         * 0000000
    009271C        001600* PROCESSED BY THE APPLICATION.                                 * 0000000
    009272C        001700*                                                               * 0000000
    009273C        001800* FOR EFFICIENCY IN TRAVERSING THE BATCH REQUEST TABLE DATA     * 0000000
    009274C        001900* BASE, WE ALWAYS EXHAUST THE REQUESTS OF ONE TYPE BEFORE       * 0000000
    009275C        002000* MOVING TO THE NEXT ONE.  WS-RQST-PROCESSED-SW TELLS US        * 0000000
    009276C        002100* WHETHER THE NEXT FETCH REQUEST FOR A GIVEN TYPE IS "FIRST"    * 0000000
    009277C        002200* (THE FIRST FETCH IN THIS RUN), "NEXT" (SUBSEQUENT FETCHES),   * 0000000
    009278C        002300* OR WHETHER ALL REQUESTS OF THAT TYPE HAVE BEEN RETRIEVED.     * 0000000
    009279C        002400*                                                               * 0000000
    009280C        002500* MORE-REQUESTS-TO-PROCESS WILL BECOME TRUE WHEN THE FIRST      * 0000000
    009281C        002600* SUCCESSFUL FETCH OF A NON-EXECUTING, NON-COMPLETED REQUEST    * 0000000
    009282C        002700* IS FOUND.  IF ALL THE REQUESTS HAVE BEEN RETRIEVED BY         * 0000000
    009283C        002800* THIS POINT, NO-MORE-REQUESTS-TO-PROCESS IS ALLOWED TO         * 0000000
    009284C        002900* STAND.                                                        * 0000000
    009285C        003000*                                                               * 0000000
    009286C        003100* IF WE END UP WITH REQUESTS TO PROCESS, PARA. 7100A-PREPARE-   * 0000000
    009287C        003200* FOR-BATCH IS PERFORMED TO ALLOW THE PROGRAMMER TO SET A       * 0000000
    009288C        003300* POINTER TO THE FIRST REQUEST, ETC.                            * 0000000
    009289C        003400*                                                               * 0000000
    009290C        003500***************************************************************** 0000000
    009291C        003600                                                                  0000000
    009292C        003700     MOVE SPACES  TO  WS-RQST-RECORD-TABLE.                       0000000  IMP 3266
    009293C        003900     SET NO-MORE-REQUESTS-TO-PROCESS  TO  TRUE.                   0000000  363
    009294C        003910     SET INVALID-PARAMETER  TO  TRUE.                             0000000  387
    009295C        004000                                                                  0000000
    009296C        004100     IF ALL-REQUESTS-RETRIEVED                                    0000000  358
    009297C     1  004200         NEXT SENTENCE                                            0000000
    009298C        004300     ELSE                                                         0000000
    009299C     1  004400         PERFORM 7010H-OBTAIN-NEXT-BRT-BATCH                      0000000  9311

    009301C        004500                                                                  0000000

    009384               *   REQUEST INFORMATION, AND STORING IT IN A SUITABLE PLACE.    * 00373300
    009385               *                                                               * 00373400
    009386               *?  IF THE PROGRAM PROCESSES BOTH BR&T AND BATCH CONTROL        * 00373500
    009387               *?  PARAMETERS, WHEN A NEW PLANT IS OBTAINED THE PROGRAMMER     * 00373600
    009388               *?  MUST SET WS-RQST-PROCESSED-SW (1) TO 'F'.  THIS WILL ALLOW  * 00373700
    009389               *?  THE BR&T PROCESSING TO LOOK FOR THE NEW BR&T REQUEST ID.    * 00373800
    009390               *?  PLEASE SEE TO DOCUMENTATION FOR FURTHER EXPLAINATION OF     * 00373900
    009391               *?  THIS PROCESSING.                                            * 00374000
    009392               *?                                                              * 00374100

    009394               *?  FLAG.  WHEN YOU VALIDATE THE NEW BATCH CONTROL PLANT OR     * 00374300
    009395               *?  WHEREVER YOU OBTAIN YOUR PLANT PROCESSING INFORMATION FROM, * 00374400
    009396               *?  IF THE FLAG IS ON, YOU CAN SET 'IN-RALPH-ED-FLAG' TO TRUE.  * 00374500
    009397               *?  THE SHELL WILL RESET THE SWITCH PRIOR TO PERFORMING THIS    * 00374600
    009398               *?  PARAGRAPH.  PLEASE SEE THE DOCUMENTATION FOR FURTHER        * 00374700

    010412                9995A-APPL-ABORT-PROCESS.                                        00407500
    010413               ***                                                               00407600
    010414               ***  ON ENTRY TO THIS PARAGRAPH, THE ABORT MESSAGE HAS BEEN       00407700
    010415               ***  FORMATTED IN HARDCOPY-ERROR.  THE SHELL HAS TRIED TO GET     00407800
    010416               ***  THE WS-PROD-SUPP-LTERM AND WS-SEC-COORD-LTERM FROM THE       00407900
    010417               ***  TABLES DATA BASE IF THE FIELDS WERE BLANK.                   00408000
    010418               ***                                                               00408100
    010419               ***  IN THIS PARAGRAPH, YOU MAY SEND THE ABORT MESSAGE VIA        00408200
    010420               ***  THE MAIL SUBSYSTEM INSTEAD OF THROUGH IMS.  YOU MAY          00408300
    010421               ***  ALSO SEND THE MESSAGE ANY WAY YOU LIKE TO DESTINATIONS       00408400
    010422               ***  IN ADDITION TO THE SUPPORT AGENCY OR SECTION COORDINATOR.    00408500
    010423               ***                                                               00408600
    010424               ***  BEFORE LEAVING, MOVE SPACES TO WS-PROD-SUPP-LTERM AND/OR     00408700
    010425               ***  WS-SEC-COORD-LTERM TO SUPPRESS THEIR USE TO RECEIVE THE      00408800
    010426               ***  HARDCOPY MESSAGE, OR REPLACE THEM WITH NON-BLANK VALUES      00408900
    010427               ***  TO ESTABLISH DIFFERENT LTERMS.                               00409000
    010428               ***                                                               00409100
    010429               ***  FOR TESTING PURPOSES, SPACES ARE MOVED TO "WS-SEC-COORD-     00409200
    010430               ***  LTERM" TO SUPPRESS PRINTING OF ABEND MESSAGES TO FORD'S      00409300
    010431               ***  ABEND PRINTER.  AS LONG AS DBUG IS ON THE ABORT MESSAGE      00409400
    010432               ***  WILL NOT PRINT AT FORD.                                      00409500
    010433               ***                                                               00409600
    010434               *    MOVE SPACES  TO  WS-SEC-COORD-LTERM.                         00409700
    010435               *    MOVE LIT-YES TO  SW-FATAL-ERROR-PRT.                         00409800
    010436               ***                                                               00409900
    010437                    CONTINUE                                                     00410000

 0CONTEXT USAGE IS INDICATED BY THE LETTER PRECEDING A PROCEDURE-NAME REFERENCE.
  THESE LETTERS AND THEIR MEANINGS ARE:
      A = ALTER (PROCEDURE-NAME)
      D = GO TO (PROCEDURE-NAME) DEPENDING ON
      E = END OF RANGE OF (PERFORM) THROUGH (PROCEDURE-NAME)
      G = GO TO (PROCEDURE-NAME)
      P = PERFORM (PROCEDURE-NAME)
      T = (ALTER) TO PROCEED TO (PROCEDURE-NAME)
      U = USE FOR DEBUGGING (PROCEDURE-NAME)
